		  <h2>Terms of Sale and Software Licence Agreement</h2>

<p>1.0&nbsp;<strong>TERMS OF SALE AND SOFTWARE LICENSE AGREEMENT </strong></p>

<p style="margin-left: 40px;">These Terms of Sale and Software License Agreement (&ldquo;Terms of Sale&rdquo;) are entered into by and between the MCI IT entity described in the following paragraphs (&ldquo;MCI IT&rdquo;) and you (&ldquo;Customer&rdquo;), for Products and Services, unless MCI IT and Customer enter into or have entered into another agreement (including but not limited to a written, click-wrap, click-and-accept or electronic agreement) regarding the purchase and license of the specific MCI IT Products or Services being purchased and such agreement is in effect at the time the applicable Purchase Order is received by MCI IT (the &ldquo;Existing Agreement&rdquo;), in which case the terms and conditions of such Existing Agreement shall govern the purchase and license of those MCI IT Products or Services.</p>

<p>1.1 <strong>DEFINITIONS</strong></p>

<p style="margin-left: 40px;">a) &nbsp;&ldquo;Affiliate&rdquo; means any corporation, firm, partnership or other entity that directly or indirectly controls, or is controlled by, or is under common control with MCI IT or Customer.</p>

<p style="margin-left: 40px;">b) &ldquo;MCI IT Branded&rdquo; means a Product or a Service bearing a trademark or service mark of MCI IT or Progress Software Inc.</p>

<p style="margin-left: 40px;">c) &ldquo;Confidential Information&rdquo; means proprietary and confidential information received by MCI IT or Customer in connection with these Terms of Sale and their relationship and is conspicuously marked as confidential, proprietary or the like or, in the case of confidential information disclosed orally, clearly identified as confidential, proprietary or the like at the time of oral disclosure and confirmed as confidential, proprietary or the like in writing within 14 days by the disclosing party.&nbsp; Such Confidential Information may include, but is not limited to, trade secrets, know how, inventions, techniques, processes, programs, schematics, software source documents, data, customer lists, financial information, and sales and marketing plans or information which the receiving party knows or has reason to know is confidential, proprietary or trade secret information of the disclosing party, as well as, in the case of MCI IT, any information posted on mci-it.co.za client zone&nbsp;(to the extent such information is not publicly accessible).</p>

<p style="margin-left: 40px;">d) &ldquo;Documentation&rdquo; means user manuals, training materials, Product descriptions and specifications, technical manuals, license agreements, supporting materials and other information relating to Products or Services offered by MCI IT, whether distributed in print, electronic, CD-ROM or video format.</p>

<p style="margin-left: 40px;">e) &ldquo;Effective Date&rdquo; means the date these Terms of Sale are electronically accepted, click-accepted or, if signed in hard copy by Customer, the date of last signature, or in the absence of any of the forgoing, these Terms of Sale shall be effective from the date an order is placed by Customer.</p>

<p style="margin-left: 40px;">f) &ldquo;Force Majeure Event&rdquo; means an event beyond the affected party&rsquo;s reasonable control, including (without limitation) accidents, severe weather events, acts of God, actions of any government agency, epidemic, pandemic, acts of terrorism, or the stability or availability of the Internet or a portion thereof.</p>

<p style="margin-left: 40px;">g) &ldquo;Hardware&rdquo; means the tangible MCI IT product acquired by Customer from MCI IT and listed on the Price List.&nbsp; Hardware does not include any tangible product listed on the Price List in the name of a third party.</p>

<p style="margin-left: 40px;">h) &ldquo;Network Services&rdquo; means any services offered by Customer, as Customer&rsquo;s primary business model, which services may include the following: access to the Internet, data and voice transmission and any other communications service furnished by Customer by means of Customer&rsquo;s communications network.</p>

<p style="margin-left: 40px;">i) &ldquo;Price List&rdquo; means the price list(s) published at mci-it.co.za applicable to the relevant MCI IT product or service to which each Purchase Order is issued by Customer.&nbsp; Products on the Price List are categorized and discounts provided by MCI IT will vary.</p>

<p style="margin-left: 40px;">j) &ldquo;Product&rdquo; means, individually or collectively as appropriate, Hardware, Software and Documentation listed on the then-current Price List.</p>

<p style="margin-left: 40px;">k) &ldquo;Purchase Order&rdquo; or &ldquo;PO&rdquo; means a written or electronic order to MCI IT for Products or Services to be provided by MCI IT under these Terms of Sale.</p>

<p style="margin-left: 40px;">l) &ldquo;Services&rdquo; means any maintenance, technical support, or any other services performed or to be performed by MCI IT, provided that &ldquo;Services&rdquo; does not include those services for which MCI IT requires a separate statement of work to be executed between the parties.</p>

<p style="margin-left: 40px;">m) &ldquo;Software&rdquo; means the machine readable (object code) version of the computer programs listed from time to time on the Price List or provided with the Hardware and made available by MCI IT for license to Customer including firmware, and any copies made, bug fixes for, updates to, or upgrades thereof.&nbsp; Software does not include any computer programs listed on the Price List in the name of a third party.</p>

<p style="margin-left: 40px;">n) &ldquo;Territory&rdquo; means the country in which Customer&rsquo;s principal place of business is located.</p>

<p><strong>2.0 SCOPE </strong></p>

<p style="margin-left: 40px;">a) These Terms of Sale set forth the terms and conditions for Customer&rsquo;s purchase of Products and Services solely for use in the Territory and solely for (i) Customer&rsquo;s internal business use</p>

<p style="margin-left: 40px;">b) Customer shall not resell to, make available for use by, or otherwise transfer title to any Product to, any end user or other third party.</p>

<p><strong>3.0 PRICES </strong></p>

<p style="margin-left: 40px;">a) Prices for Products and Services shall be those specified in MCI IT&rsquo;s then current Price List, less any applicable Price List category or individual Product or Service based discount(s) granted by MCI IT in a separate addendum in effect at the time of acceptance of the Purchase Order by MCI IT, or in accordance with an applicable, valid written price quotation, if any, submitted by MCI IT to Customer for such Products or Services.</p>

<p style="margin-left: 40px;">b) All prices are exclusive of any freight, handling and shipping insurance charges, taxes, fees and duties or other similar amounts, however designated, including without limitation value added, sales and withholding taxes which are levied or based upon the prices, charges or upon these Terms of Sale.&nbsp; Customer shall pay any taxes related to Products and Services provided pursuant to these Terms of Sale (except for taxes based on MCI IT&rsquo;s net income) or shall present an exemption certificate acceptable to all relevant taxing authorities.&nbsp; Applicable taxes shall, to the extent practical, be billed as a separate item on the invoice.</p>

<p><strong>4.0 ORDERS </strong></p>

<p style="margin-left: 40px;">a) Customer shall purchase or license Products or Services by issuing a Purchase Order, signed, if requested by MCI IT, or (in the case of electronic transmission) sent by its authorized representative, indicating specific Products and Services, MCI IT Product numbers, quantity, unit price, total purchase price, shipping instructions, requested shipping dates, bill-to and ship-to addresses, tax exempt certifications, if applicable, contract reference, and identity of the end user for each Product and Service.&nbsp; No contingency contained on any Purchase Order shall be binding upon MCI IT.&nbsp; The terms of these Terms of Sale shall apply, regardless of any additional or conflicting terms on any Purchase Order or other correspondence or documentation submitted by Customer to MCI IT, and any such additional or conflicting terms are deemed rejected by MCI IT.</p>

<p style="margin-left: 40px;">b) MCI IT shall use commercially reasonable efforts to provide order acknowledgement information within three (3) business days for all Purchase Orders placed with MCI IT or within ten (10) business days of receipt for Purchase Orders placed by any other method.&nbsp; Upon and subject to credit approval by MCI IT following MCI IT&rsquo;s receipt of any Purchase Order, MCI IT Customer Service will review and accept or decline any or all Purchase Orders for the MCI IT products and services placed on any MCI IT electronic platform, and no other person is authorized to accept Purchase Orders on behalf of MCI IT.&nbsp; MCI IT Customer Service may accept a Purchase Order even if some of the information required by Section 4a above is missing or incomplete.</p>

<p style="margin-left: 40px;">c) Customer may defer Product shipment for up to thirty (30) days from the original shipping date scheduled by MCI IT, provided written or electronic notice (issued, in either case, by an authorized representative of Customer) is received by MCI IT at least ten (10) days before the originally scheduled shipping date.&nbsp; Cancelled Purchase Orders, rescheduled shipments or Product customisation requested by Customer less than ten (10) days before the original scheduled shipping date shall be subject to (a) acceptance by MCI IT, and (b) a charge of fifteen percent (15%) of the total invoice amount relating to the affected Products or services.&nbsp; MCI IT reserves the right to reschedule shipment in cases of customisation requested by Customer within ten (10) days of scheduled shipment. <strong>No cancellation shall be accepted by MCI IT where Products are purchased with implementation services, including design, customization or installation services, except as may be set forth in the agreement or statement of work under which the services are to be rendered.</strong></p>

<p><strong>5.0 SHIPPING AND DELIVERY </strong></p>

<p style="margin-left: 40px;">a) Scheduled shipping dates will be assigned by MCI IT as close as practicable to Customer&rsquo;s requested date based on MCI IT&rsquo;s then-current lead times for the Products and services.&nbsp; MCI IT will communicate scheduled <strong>shipping dates in the order acknowledgement or on mci-it.co.za website</strong> unless given written instruction by Customer, MCI IT shall select the carrier.</p>

<p style="margin-left: 40px;">b) Shipping options available as well as applicable shipment terms on mci-it.co.za website.&nbsp; The selected shipping option shall be indicated on the Purchase Order.&nbsp; Where applicable, Customer shall pay the shipping and handling charges in addition to the purchase price for the Products and Services, which will be included in remittance and/or commercial invoices issued by MCI IT.&nbsp; Title and risk of loss shall transfer from MCI IT to Customer and delivery shall be deemed to occur in accordance with the Shipping Terms Conditions.&nbsp; Customer shall be responsible for all freight; handling and insurance charges subsequent to delivery were applicable.</p>

<p style="margin-left: 40px;">c) Where Customer places orders on any MCI IT Affiliate (Outside South Africa) other than MCI IT, Customer shall pay any invoices issued by such entity with respect to such orders and the delivery terms agreed with such entity shall apply.&nbsp; Different shipping terms may apply to such Purchase Orders as set forth in the Shipping Terms Conditions or otherwise as set out on mci-it.co.za</p>

<p style="margin-left: 40px;">d) Customer shall assume responsibility for compliance with applicable export laws and regulations, including the preparation and filing of shipping documentation necessary for export clearance.&nbsp; This also applies in cases where Customer requests in its Purchase Order delivery of Products and Services to Customer&rsquo;s forwarding agent or another representative in the country of shipment.&nbsp; Customer agrees not to use any export licenses owned by MCI IT or any of its Affiliates.</p>

<p style="margin-left: 40px;">e) For shipments under FCA (designation of the location of a seller to deliver goods) as per the Shipping Terms Conditions, Customer specifically agrees to provide MCI IT with the complete name and address of each End User either</p>

<p style="margin-left: 80px;">(i) in the Purchase Order issued, or</p>

<p style="margin-left: 80px;">(ii) in writing within five (5) days of receiving a request by MCI IT, and other information required under these Terms of Sale or requested by MCI IT.&nbsp; Export clearance will ensure utilizing MCI IT&rsquo;s general global export licenses or in the case a general global license does not include the listed End User destination, then individual export licenses must be obtained prior to export.&nbsp; Customer accepts any additional delays caused by the export licensing process as well as delays to comply with conditions of the individual export license.</p>

<p style="margin-left: 40px;">f) MCI IT shall not be liable for any loss, damage, or penalty for delay in delivery or for failure to give notice of any delay.&nbsp; Except in accordance with the applicable shipping terms set forth in these Terms of Sale, MCI IT shall not have any liability in connection with shipment, nor shall the carrier be deemed to be an agent of MCI IT.</p>

<p style="margin-left: 40px;">g) All sales are final.&nbsp; Except as provided in MCI IT&rsquo;s warranty statements, MCI IT does not accept returns unless</p>

<p style="margin-left: 80px;">(i) MCI IT shipped a product other than as specified in the Purchase Order,</p>

<p style="margin-left: 80px;">(ii) such Product is unopened, and</p>

<p style="margin-left: 80px;">(iii) the Product is returned in accordance with MCI IT&rsquo;s then current RMA (Return Merchandise Authorisation) policy and procedures.</p>

<p><strong>6.0 PAYMENT </strong></p>

<p style="margin-left: 40px;">Upon and subject to credit approval by MCI IT, payment terms shall be seven (7) days from shipping date or otherwise indicated.&nbsp; All payments shall be made in the currency of the Price List applicable to the Purchase Order or in one of the local currencies made available by MCI IT, subject to Customer and MCI IT entering into a local currency agreement.&nbsp; If at any time Customer is delinquent in the payment of any invoice, or is otherwise in breach of these Terms of Sale, MCI IT may, in its discretion, and without prejudice to its other rights, withhold shipment (including partial shipments) of any order, require Customer to prepay for further shipments, and/or withhold the provision of Services, until complete payment has been received.&nbsp; Any sum not paid by Customer when due shall bear interest from the due date to the date of payment, such interest to run day to day and after as well as before any judgment at a rate of</p>

<p style="margin-left: 80px;">(i) prime plus 12 per cent per annum or</p>

<p style="margin-left: 80px;">(ii) the maximum rate permitted by law, whichever is less.</p>

